    {

      "source": [

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "reshaped_images_removed_mean = data.reshape(400, 4096)\n",
        "\n",

        "\n",
        "pca = PCA(n_components=400)\n",

        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"

            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 5
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [

    {

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Compute the variance contributed by the first d principal components and later use that to decide how many principal components to use."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VHsJRUMKe-vH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "explained_var = []\n",
        "running_sum = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "eigval_sum = 0\n",
        "for j in range(len(eigenvals)):\n",
        "  eigval_sum += eigenvals[j]\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(len(eigenvals)):\n",
        "  running_sum += eigenvals[i]\n",
        "  explained_var.append(running_sum/eigval_sum)"
      ],
      "metadata": {

    {

        "d) Analyzing eigenvalues and explaining why 400th eigenvalue is zero."

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Scikit Learn's implementation of principal component analysis takes the minimum of the number of samples and the dimensionality of data as the number of components. Hence for a sample of 400 x 64 x 64 images, it will take the sample size of 400 which is smaller than the dimensionality of 4096 (64 x 64) to produce 400 components."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YIJFtc0IbA-b"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Each principal component contributes variance encoding information about the underlying dataset. The amount of variance encoded can be shown mathematically through the principal component's corresponding eigenvalue. A higher eigenvalue means more variance is attributed by this component. There are a finite number of components which when combined will cumulatively all contribute to a maximum variance of one in the dataset. Hence for components sorted by eigenvalue, each corresponding one will have a lower eigenvalue until the last component. The last component’s eigenvalue will be extremely small, since almost all variance has already been explained by prior components. This is evidently the case as shown above where the eigenvalue is so small that it is negligible."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jmCmPjTeilT4"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "g) Reconstruct image using principal components"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SUZUyGAXcPvI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#Define function to perform PCA reconstruction\n",
        "\n",
        "def pcaReconstruction(img, comp):\n",
        "  reconstructed_img = np.zeros((64, 64))\n",
        "\n",
        "  for component in range(comp):\n",
        "\n",
        "    #Retrieve each eigenvector, formulate into array, take transpose and combine\n",
        "    #Then multiply each transformation by the 100th mean-removed image sample\n",
        "    #Add it on and repeat process over each eigenvector as per reconstruction formula \n",
        "    \n",
        "    e = np.rot90(pca.components_[component].reshape(64, 64), k=1, axes=(1,0))\n",
        "    e_T = np.transpose(e)\n",
        "    e_e_T = np.matmul(e, e_T)\n",
        "    pc_img = np.matmul(e_e_T, rem_mean_images[img])\n",
        "    reconstructed_img = np.add(reconstructed_img, pc_img)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # #Complex numbers get involved in matrix operations, hence set casting to unsafe to deal with it\n",
        "    # transformed_img = np.add(transformed_img, e_e_T*org_img, casting=\"unsafe\")\n",
        "  \n",
        "  return reconstructed_img"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UzPmalY3ZLSe"
      },
      "execution_count": 16,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#List comprehension to compute reconstructed images for 100th image using 10, 100, 200, 399 principal components\n",
        "\n",
        "reconstructed_img = [pcaReconstruction(99, i) for i in [10, 100, 200, 399]]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pjWeIMOE92ST"
      },
      "execution_count": 17,
